eplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=891.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DKNY</span><hr size=1> <br>  Do you have any ammending of points on the fly as loot sits and approaches rot?  It's easy to say that an item which will rot provides no use to anyone... but I can imagine no drop items which are likely to rot but have beneficial stats such as resists or such.  A rogue might go for an item with ac in the rare instances where they are a group's main tank, but would never actually spend hard earned points on such an item...<br><br>  Maeghant Tuskbone (level meaningless) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub78.ezboard.com/urolemeggido.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Role Meggido</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/20/01 12:43:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=891.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DKNY</span><hr size=1> Yeah that is what I was wondering.  It would seem that some system the no-drop loot dropped in value in rounds till it reached some value that someone would want it would make sense.  This would also seem to address the inflation issue a little bit.<br><br>Very interesting post btw. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub78.ezboard.com/uwendolynkeplegrobal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wendolyn KeplegrobAL</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.wired-cafe.com/images/wendhead.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/20/01 6:06:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=891.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.wired-cafe.com/images/wendside.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DKNY</span><hr size=1> Officers adjust the value of loot sometimes... but it's really hard to change the cost of loot in general especially when a lot of people have already paid a given amount for it in the past... Like the RSSS for example... it's 8 DKP I think... but no one is going to pay 8 when they can get a priceless spear from ST for free the next day.  It might make sense to drop the price so that an RSSS won't rot next time, but in order to keep some amount of integrity and fairness to the system it will most likely just rot.  Twinks that have VP keys but no sleepers keys might decide to pay and loot it... however I see most VP weapons as novelty now and unless it costs 1 or 2 points it's prolly gonna poof on the corpse.  I guess we'll see how the evade nerf goes... might have to go back to high damage high delay items to stay alive in which case an RSSS would be nice.<br><br>Caster gear on the other hand will always sell like hotcakes... never really have a problem there go figure :P Thx class reward balance... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub78.ezboard.com/ufumindrachejager.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FuminDrachejager</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/20/01 8:09:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=891.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Issues...</span><hr size=1> A month ago we made some radical changes in our guild (Talisman on the Tunare server) and we've basically become a guild that is focused around doing the big raids.  We decided to go to a system like DKP.  I basically used your rules and made a few adjustments here and there... also went through the past histories of your members to get some starting points values.<br><br>First, I want to commend your officers on the system.  I think it's really great.  Loot on Tunare in the old days (5 weeks ago, hehehe) was done by the raid leader in a loot council.  It was a big pain in the arse as there would be a lot of upset people all the time.<br><br>The biggest problem I've seen is the unwillingness of people to let things rot.   They may not want to pay even a single point for an item, but if you give it to them for free then they end up using it.  There is this big stigma to letting somethign rot right now so if we dont' give it away for free then people are shocked, and if I do I feel we have created a system that is abusable.  We have one SK for example.  He could concievably get every SK item for free just by insisting that he doesn't want to pay for it.<br><br>We've also done a couple of Western Wastes raids and people dont' want to pay anything for anythign that isn't at Peerless or Matchless.  Even though some of the Worked stuff is worth tons on the open market, and would be big upgrades for people.  I don't want to let stuff like that go for free because then there are people that have 3 twinks that love those sorts of items and then there are folks that have no twinks and would never take it.  I don't even know what to do w/ it.<br><br>Our guild vault already has a lot of high end items.... I can only wonder what you guys have... what do you do with it all?<br><br>Laters,<br><br>Fumin Drachejager<br>Warlord of Talisman<br>Tunare <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub78.ezboard.com/uwendolynkeplegrobal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wendolyn KeplegrobAL</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.wired-cafe.com/images/wendhead.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/20/01 8:56:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=891.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.wired-cafe.com/images/wendside.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Issues...</span><hr size=1> I think we have 1 active ranger in the guild... and he rarely shows up nowadays.  If a ranger item dropped and he didn't want to pay for it... it would rot.  People would prolly frown at him for it but it's his decision.  We all respect the fact that you earn every point and as a result you earn the right to spend those points however you want.<br><br>As for WW loot, anything that is not matchless is not DKP.  I think like 1 matchless item has dropped... a mask I think and it was 0.5 DKP just cuz it was &quot;the best&quot; if for no other reason.  All the WW loot goes to our twinks now basically.  I think some ppl just created characters so they could outfit a twink in full WW armor, except for the breastplates.  They cost 1 for worked, 2 for reinforced, 3 or for heavy I think.  We haven't gotten peerless or matchless BPs yet but I think they will cost anywhere between 5 and 8.<br><br>We have a trade forum on our board which ppl use to sell and buy items on Mith Marr.  Among those threads is a post from Hobben which lists all the guild items we have for sale... various Trak BPs and VS legs... old cazic nag vox loot... etc.  People contact him via email and purchase what they want.  Prices are not listed, since they are subject to market changes.  Hobb has easily over 1 Million plat in his bank right now...he basically holds the guild vault but I swear he skims off the top!  Guess we are just saving up for a rainy day... who knows.  At any rate, that's what happens to most of our high end excess loot that no guild members want. <p></p>